DUKE10095588

Flora of North Carolina (U.S.A.)

Diapensiaceae
*Galax aphylla* L.

Terrestrial plants with taproot and glossy,
leathery leaves placed in basal rosettes.
Inflorescence centrally places spikes with
small white flowers and dry black many
seeded fruit.

Orange County, Hillsborough, Occoneechee
Mountain State Natural Area, along the Eno
River. Along I-85, exit 164, North, near fly-
over of Orange Grove Road, off Virginia
Cates Road.
36° 04′N 79° 08′W ± 220 m (700 ft) alt.

Northern slope of Occoneechee Mountain,
Panthers Den. Forest with large boulders
with a canopy of e.a. *Quercus*, *Fagus*,
*Liquidambar*, *Liriodendron*, *Sassafras* and
*Lindera*.

leg.: Maarten J. M. Christenhusz 3782
with Jordan S. Metzgar & Emily J. Fraker
September 11, 2004.
